title: Let Them Theory - Family
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Family is often the "final boss" of the "Let Them" theory due to deep-rooted roles.

* '''Release the "Shoulds"''': Stop fighting the reality of who your family members are. Accept the people you have, not the ones you wish for.
* '''No Emotional Babysitting''': You are not the family's emotional thermostat. Let them be in a bad mood or passive-aggressive without absorbing it.
* '''Observer vs. Participant''': Create a "protective bubble." Watch the family drama without being consumed by it.
* '''The "Let Me" Boundary''': "They are going to judge my choices. Let them. Now, let me decide how much time I spend with them."